text.section:
The program shall provide 3 hours of instruction in:
The hazards of driving while impaired or intoxicated;
The criminal penalties and administrative sanctions for alcohol and drug related motor vehicle violations;
The medical, biological, and psychological effects of the consumption of alcohol and drugs and their impact on the operation of a motor vehicle; and
Any other drug and alcohol related information that the Administration determines would be beneficial to applicants for a driver's license.
